It’s is a misnomer to state that’s anti-vaxxers defy categorization. There are three very clear categories of individuals: 
1. People of color who have legitimate concerns about medical science as a result of their exploitation over decades by the white medical establishment;
2. Trump’s base whose distrust of all institutions in public life has been fanned for political advantage by a Republican Party that wraps itself in the flag but is undoubtedly the most unpatriotic component of our society;
3. Uninformed, middle class and upper middle class white folks who are otherwise reasonably well-educated but have fallen victim to bad science around vaccines that traces its roots back to the 1990s Lancet article linking vaccines to autism. 

Knowing who is susceptible to anti-vaccine propaganda at least allows you to address it. Throwing up your hands and saying anti-vaxxers are everywhere admits defeat before the battle has begun. Just sayin.

