OK, so Trump trashed Obama’s playbook for pandemic response and dismantled the WH response team. At least we could observe the best success records from other countries like Germany, Taiwan, New Zealand, Scotland (all led by women), S.Korea, and Australia. The playbook ain’t that complicated in theory:

- Shut down early and open slowly;
- Test widely, make testing easy and provide results rapidly;
- Contact trace effectively and quarantine those that become infected;
- Achieve high compliance to mask wearing, hand washing, social distancing;
- Provide adequate nationwide funding for all parts of the healthcare provider chain to cope with the crises, including widespread testing, PPE, and hospital solvency;
- Provide adequate funding for working class families to stay at home during the lockdown;
- Do not politicize the pandemic or any of the above initiatives to address the pandemic - this would only result in noncompliance.  Do not corruptly misappropriate funding meant to save lives;

Sadly, Trump’s response to these straightforward, observably effective steps is no, no, no, no, no, no, and no.  Instead he orders a fleet of proverbial buses to throw scapegoats under - his latest order appears to be for one to sacrifice Dr Fauci.

@Cara This line of thinking is maddening. I want my kids back in school desperately, but not at the risk of anyone’s health. Yes, people will get Covid in school and out, you are correct about that. But to open schools before we have driven down the infection rate is throwing gas on the fire. Why is this so hard for some of us to see?
As a country, we messed up. Now we need a do-over. We have to lock down and get the numbers low. We have to then be able to test effectively enough to knock down cases where they flare up.  That’s how other countries are doing it. 
Sometimes simplicity is very hard.
